commands to install the packages

commands to install containerd
1 .  sudo swapoff -a
   16  vi /etc/fstab
   17  cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf
   18  overlay
   19  br_netfilter
   20  EOF
   21  cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf
   22  overlay
   23  br_netfilter
   24  EOF
   25  
   41  sudo modprobe overlay
   43  sudo modprobe br_netfilter
   44  cat <<EOF | sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/k8s.conf
   45  net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables =1
   46  net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables =1
   47  net.ipv4.ip_forward =1
   48  EOF
   49  sudo sysctl --system
   50  apt-get install -y containerd
   51  sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd
   52  sudo containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml
   53  sudo sed -i 's/       SystemdCgroup = false/   SystemdCgroup = true/' /etc/containerd/config.toml
   54  grep 'systemdCgroup = true' /etc/containerd/config.toml
   55  sudo systemctl restart containerd

   install kubeadm, kubectl

   sudo apt-get update
   sudo apt-get install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gpg
   curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.28/deb/Release.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg
   echo 'deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.28/deb/ /' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list
   sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl


Joining nodes to master node

hit this command in master node " kubeadm token create --print-join-command" - 
that will give us a command and we can copy paste this in worker node

now hit the kubectl get nodes ( list the nodes in master node)

kubectl get pods --all-namespaces --watch ( this is will list all pods in all namespaces in a cluster
)